tape the holes.&amp;nbsp; If you built it by the tek, it will work.&amp;nbsp; However, if you only used two to three inches of perlite, and only drilled holes on five sides, and spent $120 to build a $10 terrarium, you didn't build it by the tek.&amp;nbsp; Fresh air exchange is the NUMBER ONE pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; You can always mist to make up for lost moisture, which you should be doing anyway.&amp;nbsp; Covering holes to get humidity at the expense of fresh air is the OPPOSITE of what you should do.&amp;nbsp; Fresh air stimulates pins and suppresses molds.&amp;nbsp; In addition, there's no way in hell your terrarium dropped to 40%.&amp;nbsp; Calibrate your hygrometer.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9964173</next>\n<prev>9963959</prev>\n<first>9959658</first>\n<last>21015711</last>\n<when>1236962832</when>\n<utime>03/13/09 07:47 PM</utime>\n</post>"}